        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 7:42PM CST by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>A period of heavy snow will significantly reduce visibility and
create snow-covered roadways across south central North Dakota
this evening. Locations impacted by this area of heavy snow
include Almont, Flasher, St. Anthony, Hazelton, Wishek, and
Ashley. Snowfall will continue to accumulate at a heavy rate
around one inch per hour in these areas through mid evening.
Snowfall will become lighter overnight, but localized storm total
snowfall accumulations of 4 to 7 inches are expected in the area
of heaviest snowfall by Saturday morning. A Winter Weather
Advisory remains in effect tonight. Be prepared for difficult
travel and reduced visibility, and be sure to check the latest
road conditions.
</description>
